“Doing things differently leads to something exceptional.” ~ Unknown 

Ok 2023, let’s do some different $#*t!!!~ Me 

•

For me, last year was a time of awakening, learning, creating & planting. I learned so much about who I am, what I want, where I want to grow to. I’m ready for new adventures, new experiences & all the peace, love, abundance & success coming my way! 2022 taught me  to focus on the end goal and not on the the current circumstance. Well, it’s a definitely a practice lol but one that I’m now conscious of! 

Own your power, know your worth & believe that you can have/do/be whatever you want and watch it all be reflected back to you!!! We can do it all!!! Don’t give up!!! Persist!!! And Dreamers, dream your biggest dreams in 2023!!! 🌟💫✨Happy New Year & beyond!!! 🎊🎉

•

It’s been a long time coming but it’s finally happening! I fought it for a very long time but I’m so happy I finally acquiesced to the message the universe was sending me on repeat. I do believe that it happened when it was supposed to & that this was the first story I was meant to tell. It’s just the beginning but it’s a beautiful starting point if I do say so myself! 🥰 

Thank you to everyone on this journey with me!! More to come soon and follow @perspectivesfilm for all the things! 🎬

“When life appears to be a maze, there is always freedom in a higher perspective. “ ~ Unknown 

•

Sometimes life can feel confusing. Like just when things are going perfectly, all of a sudden there’s a sharp left or a seemingly dead end. Obviously, this can feel frustrating but one thing I’ve been learning in life lately is it’s not what happens that’s important but how you react to it. If you are unwavering in your desires, assumptions and belief then whatever the immediate circumstances are will become irrelevant. Moreover, will become merely steps on the journey to your dreams! Staying rooted in your knowing isn’t always easy but view it as a practice, just like physical fitness, and you will continue to exercise and strengthen that muscle! Decide what you want & let it guide you so fervently that every twist & turn becomes laughable! We can do this, Dreamers!!! Keep dreaming & persisting!!! Let’s get it ALLLLLL!!! ✨

“Being vulnerable is the only way to allow your heart to feel true pleasure.” ~ Bob Marley 

•

This is so true! In art. In friendship. In love. It’s one of the biggest paradoxical lessons that life will teach us. Being “tough” can quell creativity, preventing you from exploring your most relatable & cathartic art. Being “strong” can keep people at arm’s length even when you really want them close. Ultimately, vulnerability is the bridge with which we build the deepest human connection. 

Admittedly, this is one of my biggest personal challenges. Even just writing this post feels scary & raw. I’m the person that people can always lean on, count on & come to for advice & support but that’s easy for me. The hard part is opening up, saying ‘this is who I am & this is what I need’ . But true courage lies in being open, true bravery lies in communication & true strength lies in vulnerability. And remember, there is no need to be afraid, the world is yours and you can have it all! Dream on Dreamers! 💫

“I went to sleep last night with a smile because I knew I’d be dreaming of you…but I woke up this morning with a smile because you weren’t a dream.” ~ Unknown 

It’s official!!! I’M MADLY IN LOVE!!! 💖 Here is the trailer to my rom-com short film & directorial debut ‘Perspectives’!! This film is my first love & on this day my funny Valentine!!! 🥰 Please watch & I hope you love the trailer as much as I do!!! 

I am so happy with & proud of this project and most of all myself! For so long I fought the idea of making a short film (it’s still a bit crazy imo) but this film is everything I wanted it to be! I learned SO much in the process of writing, producing & directing (and post-supervising 🥵 lol) this story. I’m a better artist, filmmaker, storyteller and even version of myself after this experience! The voice I always knew I had inside has finally been expressed & actualized and I absolutely adore it!! I’m so thankful that I invested in myself & gave myself this opportunity to grow!!! I’m just as grateful for all of the people in my life that helped me achieve this huge milestone! @watchjazzy @_mikemerrill_ @ashannabri @christianhoward Greg Anderson @treyhaleytds @nikayatds @iamcarlweber @nataschahopkins @emily_mungun @jeanquest @vududaddy @dpken @myrabarrera @aaronfonts @gaylaofla @abriannalinell  @ashlynayersmua @thefoundationpost @artistryinsound and so many more! If you gave me notes, worked on the shoot or even just listened to me overthink during the process, I truly appreciate you!!! 💞

From page to screen the journey has been magical! ✨ It was tough at times and, of course, the Virgo in me can see where improvements could be still be made 😵‍💫 but this film is beautiful, personal and so very “Veronica”! 💗 We are currently doing the festival circuit & having great success! Many screenings coming up so stay tuned!!! Remember, we are already everything that we want to be! It is done!!! Just believe it!!! Love on Lovers & Dream on Dreamers!!! 💖💫💖💫

“Be the sun breaking through the clouds.” - A.D. Posey

•

I love this photo because it’s a visual representation of how life can feel sometimes: grey, cloudy and even tumultuous like the crashing waves. But you can decide to be and to see the sunshine breaking through it all with brazen impudence! You choose! 🌤️

Here in LA, we have been dealing with some wild storms (heavy rain, wind, hail & even snow! 🤯) but in the midst of all that there has been so much light, love & joy bursting through! Can’t wait to share it all with you so stay tuned! 😆 Remember, take control of your thoughts and your perspective; it will change your narrative and your experience! What life do you want to live? Decide and so it is! The universe has us, just control your mind! Believe, persist & dream on Dreamers!!! 💫

“It’s ironic how you feel most alive when your heart skips a few beats.” ~ Unknown

•

I’m so excited about tomorrow that I’m all butterflies & adrenaline highs! I love seeing my stories, characters & visual aesthetic come to life on the big screen! It’s a rush every time but something about this one feels extra magical! ✨ However, the last few days, I’ve been feeling a bit odd, but not in a particularly bad way. Like I’m hungry but don’t have an appetite. Like time is flying but also creeping by. Like I have so many details to attend to but have already done everything I can think of. Am I nervous? No. Am I scared? No. Am I worried? No. 

Then what is it? I realized I had felt this feeling before. Some of you may not know but I’m also a dancer & coach. Once, when I was training for a performance I said I had stage fright. A long-time circus performer & trusted colleague offered me an impactful perspective. It was a complete game changer. He told me that fear/anxiety manifest in the body the same way as adrenaline: sweaty palms, shaky hands, shortness of breath. BUT, he revealed, if you’re prepared then you’re not nervous, it’s just adrenaline. It was so simple! I was prepared for that performance & I’m more than prepared now. I am proud of this film. My cast, crew & I worked hard & created something very special. So tomorrow, I will ride my adrenaline high, welcome my butterflies, & celebrate all that we have accomplished! Thank you to everyone who has supported me, this vision & this journey. You are appreciated! So much more to come! Let’s go!!! ⚡️

Now, I wonder if I can get some sleep?? 🤣 Sweet dreams, Dreamers!!! ✨

“All flowers are beautiful in their own way, and that’s like women too.” ~ Miranda Kerr

•

There are far more ways to be beautiful other than aesthetically. Beauty is a concept as nuanced and multifaceted as the human experience itself. It lies in the journey, the experience, the lesson and of course the eye of the beholder. True & lasting beauty is deeper that the surface and radiates from within. On this #internationalwomensday I celebrate all of the women in my life and all their infinite dimensions of beauty!! 💖

I was raised by an incredible woman who was stunning to the eye but what was most magical about her was who she was on the inside. She was warm, giving, nurturing, strong, wise, humble, brilliant, supportive, generous, kind… I could go on & on forever. She showed me by example the kind of woman I strive to be every day. She touched everyone she crossed paths with and left their lives better. Now that’s goals. I wish that more of you reading this could have known her & her magic. I lost her many years ago now, but I’m truly grateful for every moment I was gifted to have her as my mother! 💜 Until we meet again, Mommy, I’ll try to treat people as you would & make you proud as I continue to live this life & manifest these dreams!  We can do it all! Dream on Dreamers! ✨

•

“The biggest adventure you can take is to live the life of your dreams.” ~ Oprah Winfrey 

•

Los Angeles, Hollywood, City of Angels, La La Land. What does the term La La Land even mean?? It’s been defined as ‘A notional place characterized by fantasy, self-absorption & blissful lack of touch with reality where people do not  truly understand what a situation is really like & think it is much better than it is.’

Well, I guess in a way this might  be true depending on your perspective, but I believe it’s really a town full of dreamers that see the world as it COULD be, who then work super hard with their blood, sweet, & tears to tell that story & share that vision with the world. 

Honestly, growing up in middle America, I knew I never belonged. Not in a way that meant I was less than but in a way that meant I was different, I saw things bigger, beyond what was “normal”. No city I ever lived in really ever fit until I came to LA. Suddenly, everyone got me. Artists, creators, storytellers and, of course, dreamers were everywhere!!! 🤩All with a different voice but definitely all with something to say. It’s the place where the oddity becomes the it factor; where the misunderstood become the magical; and where the voice becomes the vision! ✨

There’s a lot going on here right now and everyday I learn something new about this wild world I’ve chosen. It’s beautiful, complex, imperfect, nuanced, risky, frustrating, illuminating, intoxicating, infuriating, inspiring & fulfilling — just like most things worth loving in this life. This is my ode to Los Angeles. I still love LA. 💜

“Every great dream begins with a dreamer. Always remember, you have within you the strength. the patience, and the passion to reach for the stars to change the world.” ~ Harriet Tubman

•

Things have been moving SO fast lately, and, while I always try to exist in a state of gratitude, I haven’t really had a moment to just sit & digest or absorb the many blessings & breakthroughs that have come my way! Much of it is still under wraps or in process, so I’ll keep the details quiet for now, but this slow down time has allowed me the opportunity to reflect on & truly appreciate my progress, my growth & most importantly my belief!

Faith, belief, knowing, conviction, decision, assumption, or whatever you choose to call it, is the very foundation of it all!! I’m beyond grateful for my amazing & supportive chosen family, my wonderful circle of friends and all those who have helped me push forth in my dreams. You are all so brilliant, talented, inspiring, generous, loving & kind! Infinite appreciation!!! Let’s keep building and creating!!!! And as always, dream on Dreamers!!! 💫

I wanna go back!!! 😩 When just another day at the office looks like this, how can you not miss it??? 🩵 Though I personally believe what’s happening has to be done & that we will all be better for it in the long run, I really miss being on set! I love teaming up with other artists & creatives to express our talents, tell our stories and live in our imaginations!!!

“Get your sparkle on. Show this world where you belong.” ~ Barbie

•

Yes, I’m late. No, I haven’t seen the movie yet. Maybe I’ve had these photos to post for waaay too long… but their moment has finally come! Yay! 

Once upon a time, someone said to me “I want a f@$&ing Black Barbie.” I responded, “Say less.” I had BEEN ready for this request all my life, growing up as a quintessential girly girl (save for a brief tomboy stint in the 4th grade, lol). I had soooo many Barbies and they all led very complicated lives filled with hijinks, antics, capers and, of course, wardrobe changes!!! I’ve been a storyteller since I can remember and I have viewed clothes as a form of self expression from a super early age. 

Just like my Barbies, I’ve always dressed for myself (and sometimes for the occasion 😉) & told the stories I wanted to tell. I’m beyond grateful to have had the support & freedom to do so! I encourage you all to explore, try something new, push outside of your comfort zone, do what interests you! Swim in the trend but make it yours, get inspired but then create your own mark! Strive to be unique & let your specialness become your relevance!! Be yourself, use YOUR voice & dream on Dreamers!!! 💫

“Sometimes it’s the journey that teaches you a lot about your destination.” ~ Drake

•

The journey of this film has been so beautiful and evolutionary! I’ve learned so much about myself, from the crazy life events that inspired the story/script, to the incredible process of shooting the film and now the empowering journey of sharing my work with audiences! 

This festival experience has been nothing short of amazing and here we are at the illustrious @bronzelens film festival to share this fun, sweet, relatable story with this wonderful group of film lovers and filmmakers! We are screening TONIGHT at 7p in ATL (link in bio)! Thank you for having us!!! Come thru if you’re in town! We hope to make you think, smile and maybe even laugh a bit!!! 

Perspectives is truly special to me. As I’ve given life to it, it has given life to me! I feel like I’ve come to understand myself more both as a woman and as artist/storyteller! This journey has really helped me find my voice & set me on the path to walking in my purpose! I will always love this film and everyone involved in bringing it to life! Thank you all!!!! 🩵

“Do your thing and don’t care if they like it.” ~ Tina Fey

•

IT’S MY BIRTHDAY AND I DO WHAT I WANT!!! 😋🥳 It has been a journey to find this space where I truly trust myself & honor my instincts & intuition. This is the next level of self love! It’s more than just mani/pedis, facials & massages (tho we deserve those too! 😉) it’s also about discovering who you are, what you want & committing to walking in that purpose. 

The above quote is fantastic advice from an amazing female creator and seems like it should be easy & obvious, but there’s a complex duality you experience as an artist where you want to express yourself but also affect others. My theory is that the best way to do both simultaneously is through authenticity. I made a promise to myself, that I would actively do more of this. Whether it’s the stories I tell, the way I dress, the hobbies I enjoy, what I post on social media, the feelings I emote, or any thing else—I’ve decided, I’m gonna do me! That’s how you truly live! We need to break out of the boxes, not put ourselves inside them!!!

We’re here to be real, not to be perfect. The Virgo in me sought perfection for a  long time, but as I evolve I realize more & more that it’s the quirks, imperfections & lessons in life that make us more resilient, interesting & relatable. 

This reminds me of the philosophy behind Kintsugi, the Japanese art of reparing broken pottery with gold. The idea is that, just like in life, when you embrace and even celebrate flaws, cracks & blemishes, you can create an even stronger, more beautiful piece of art. So tell your story, use your voice, speak your truth, feel yourself, live your life & as always dream on Dreamers!!! 💫

“What sunshine is to flowers, smiles are to humanity.” ~ Joseph Addison

•

I love the idea & the experience of being the sunshine in the world, bringing light & love to everyone you encounter! It’s in this way we can make life better, easier, happier - incrementally, every day! Give a smile, a hug or a kind word & watch the good vibes ripple through your day! ✨

Sometimes this world we live in feels like it’s spinning out of control with darkness & pain. We can see all of this & then still DECIDE to be an instrument of change, a creator of joy! Be considerate & consistent! Pour hope & positivity into those around you & appreciate those who sow the same in you! Together we can make the world better! Give love, receive love, be love! And of course, dream on Dreamers!!! 💫

P.S. Max (my puppy nephew) says: “Don’t forget to stop & smell the flowers!” on slide 2 🌸🌺

•
